Well, it must be this evil house
hiding my clothes,

01:05:55.397 --> 01:05:57.037
trying to turn me against you.

01:05:57.117 --> 01:05:58.637
Well, don't let it.

01:05:59.197 --> 01:06:00.517
Here it is.

01:06:02.158 --> 01:06:05.598
That looks a little big. Let me guess.
An ex-boyfriend's.

01:06:08.078 --> 01:06:11.359
Sweetheart, there was no one before you.

01:06:11.399 --> 01:06:13.519
You were my first.

01:06:13.599 --> 01:06:16.800
On our wedding night,
you remember how scared I was?

01:06:19.720 --> 01:06:23.040
Hey, are we supposed to bring something
to this party?

01:06:27.481 --> 01:06:31.602
DIANA: You are so... You're so
fashion-phobic. It's great. I love it.

01:06:31.682 --> 01:06:32.642
With the tie on?

01:06:32.682 --> 01:06:35.442
You're the best-Iooking guy here.
It looks great. Enjoy it.

01:06:35.522 --> 01:06:37.242
- Thank you, dear.
- It's okay.

01:06:37.322 --> 01:06:39.403
Well, listen, regarding this house,

01:06:39.483 --> 01:06:42.123
I mean,
Chloe and Oscar need a place to live.

01:06:42.163 --> 01:06:45.043
And if you find some great place,
I'll help them out.

01:06:45.123 --> 01:06:47.044
We don't even have to let them know,
you know?

01:06:47.124 --> 01:06:48.484
I'm on it.

01:06:48.524 --> 01:06:49.524
- I think I found something.
- MAN: David!

01:06:49.604 --> 01:06:52.644
I found a house with a great neighborhood.

01:06:53.485 --> 01:06:54.605
Michael, nice to see you.

01:06:54.685 --> 01:06:57.685
- WOMAN: How are you?
- Good, good, good.

01:06:57.765 --> 01:07:01.006
That sounds good. You all right?

01:07:01.046 --> 01:07:03.366
I'm gonna go get a drink.
Do you want anything?

01:07:03.406 --> 01:07:04.846
Just a beer, please.

01:07:04.926 --> 01:07:06.406
- Hey, Scott, how you doing?
- Hey.

01:07:06.446 --> 01:07:08.647
- White wine.
- Thank you so much.

01:07:09.647 --> 01:07:10.727
Diana Croce?

01:07:11.567 --> 01:07:13.647
- I'm sorry?
- Karen Watson.

01:07:13.727 --> 01:07:17.008
My husband, Dave, and I bought a house
from you a few years ago.

01:07:17.568 --> 01:07:21.128
Oh, right. The two-story Georgian.

01:07:21.168 --> 01:07:23.729
- Exactly.
- On Walnut Street.

01:07:23.809 --> 01:07:27.930
- So you're still happy with the house?
- Oh, well, we love it. At least I do.

01:07:28.010 --> 01:07:31.931
David's just so busy.

01:07:32.011 --> 01:07:33.731
He's not around much.

01:07:36.211 --> 01:07:38.692
I'm... I'm sorry. Could you excuse me?

01:07:42.492 --> 01:07:44.612
I left the house, I asked my wife,
"Do you have the directions?"

01:07:44.692 --> 01:07:45.693
She said, "I don't have the directions."

01:07:45.773 --> 01:07:47.013
I'm like, "Well, I don't have the directions."

01:07:47.093 --> 01:07:49.453
So we get in the car and start driving
and I use my little thing,

01:07:49.533 --> 01:07:51.373
and I press the button
and put the address in

01:07:51.413 --> 01:07:53.174
and I start going.
It says, "Make a right. Make a right."

01:08:00.855 --> 01:08:01.935
Diana.

01:08:03.055 --> 01:08:04.575
Hello, David.

01:08:07.936 --> 01:08:11.176
That's... That's my shirt you're wearing.

01:08:11.256 --> 01:08:13.976
Yes, it is, as a matter of fact.

01:08:15.417 --> 01:08:17.136
Do you want it back?

01:08:20.417 --> 01:08:22.298
No, it's a little late for that.

01:08:22.337 --> 01:08:23.778
You know that was
a birthday present from Karen.

01:08:23.858 --> 01:08:25.618
No, I didn't know that.

01:08:25.658 --> 01:08:27.618
And besides,
there are hundreds of shirts like this

01:08:27.698 --> 01:08:29.179
walking around Portland, David.

01:08:29.259 --> 01:08:31.179
But that one's got a button missing
from the left collar.

01:08:31.259 --> 01:08:36.499
Yeah. Well, I'm sorry
about this hideous mess that I've created.

01:08:36.540 --> 01:08:40.859
And don't worry. It's gonna be okay. Just...

01:08:42.779 --> 01:08:46.100
Tell her that what happened between us
was a mistake

01:08:46.180 --> 01:08:48.941
and this whole thing is over.

01:08:49.020 --> 01:08:51.662
She loves you. She'll forgive you.

01:08:55.582 --> 01:08:56.983
It's not over.

01:08:59.344 --> 01:09:00.504
KAREN: David?

01:09:02.224 --> 01:09:03.783
We need to leave.

01:09:28.707 --> 01:09:30.028
- Oh, right, we're moving.
- Inside.

01:09:30.108 --> 01:09:32.188
- Yes, we're moving.
- This is the last of it?

01:09:32.228 --> 01:09:33.188
I think so.

01:09:33.268 --> 01:09:34.548
- I'm hungry.
- You're hungry?

01:09:34.627 --> 01:09:35.868
- What're you gonna make?
- Should I cook something?

01:09:35.908 --> 01:09:37.109
Your famous toast?

01:09:37.189 --> 01:09:38.109
(LAUGHING)

01:09:48.750 --> 01:09:50.871
- Hello, buddy.
- Nice place you got here.

01:09:50.951 --> 01:09:53.151
Yeah, you call this home?

01:10:01.152 --> 01:10:02.672
Sorry, buddy.

01:10:16.514 --> 01:10:19.955
All right, pull up, Eric, and Lee,
square up by the tree.

01:10:21.195 --> 01:10:22.435
Hit me.

01:10:24.075 --> 01:10:25.675
OSCAR: Good one, man.

01:10:27.917 --> 01:10:31.277
- I'm out for a second.
- All right, let's keep it going.

01:10:31.357 --> 01:10:32.517
Good job on that.

01:10:32.557 --> 01:10:34.277
Thought you hated sports.

01:10:34.317 --> 01:10:36.318
Is it true, what I heard?

01:10:39.798 --> 01:10:40.958
Yeah.

01:10:43.919 --> 01:10:45.719
You moved out?

01:10:47.759 --> 01:10:48.959
Yeah.

01:10:50.800 --> 01:10:53.320
The day after the barbecue, actually.

01:10:55.600 --> 01:10:57.441
Why didn't you call me?

01:10:59.441 --> 01:11:01.321
Because you're married.

01:11:18.764 --> 01:11:22.484
See my little jig there?
Got my water bottle. What's wrong?

01:11:25.684 --> 01:11:27.285
- Shit.
- Yeah.

01:11:43.287 --> 01:11:45.087
MOVER: The dolly's
in the truck, right, Dave?

01:11:48.768 --> 01:11:50.008
Sir?

01:11:50.048 --> 01:11:51.448
That'll do it.

01:12:03.651 --> 01:12:05.651
<i>BRADLEY: It seems like
I'm just this transition</i>

01:12:05.731 --> 01:12:08.931
for women
on their way to something better.

01:12:10.371 --> 01:12:12.732
At least it was a man this time.

01:12:16.332 --> 01:12:19.773
- I thought that might be a consolation.
- It's not.

01:12:19.853 --> 01:12:22.093
- Sorry.
- It's worse.

01:12:22.533 --> 01:12:23.933
(BRADLEY JR. WHIMPERS)

01:12:24.213 --> 01:12:27.574
How do I make a change?
I can't go through this again.

01:12:27.654 --> 01:12:30.854
Harry, I swear to God, I'll lose my mind.

01:12:30.934 --> 01:12:34.655
Oh, shit. Bradley, listen.

01:12:34.735 --> 01:12:36.655
You just gotta stay alert.

01:12:37.575 --> 01:12:38.855
What does that mean?

01:12:38.935 --> 01:12:42.856
Well, everything we need to know
is going on right in front of our eyes.

01:12:42.936 --> 01:12:46.896
Yeah, we have our illusions about people,
our hopes,

01:12:46.976 --> 01:12:49.057
and they can blind us.

01:12:49.137 --> 01:12:52.857
But the end is always right there
in the beginning.

01:12:56.938 --> 01:13:00.258
Kathryn said I never saw her.

01:13:01.538 --> 01:13:04.259
Maybe I never saw Diana either.

01:13:04.339 --> 01:13:08.819
I was just looking
for some piece of happiness,

01:13:08.899 --> 01:13:12.300
so I closed my eyes and jumped.

01:13:12.380 --> 01:13:14.700
- Okay, so next time...
- Don't jump, I know.

01:13:14.780 --> 01:13:19.221
No, no, no, no, no. Jump!
Jump, but with your eyes open.

01:13:22.181 --> 01:13:24.422
Come on, Bradley.

01:13:24.462 --> 01:13:26.342
Go for a walk?

01:13:26.422 --> 01:13:28.062
This way. Come on.

01:13:28.263 --> 01:13:29.223
(BARKS)

01:13:29.303 --> 01:13:30.423
What?

01:13:33.304 --> 01:13:38.104
<i>Was it just to
keep me guessing</i>

01:13:40.425 --> 01:13:44.105
<i>For a means to the end?</i>

01:13:47.146 --> 01:13:48.066
(WOMAN LAUGHING)

01:13:49.106 --> 01:13:50.866
<i>Ghost</i>

01:14:01.268 --> 01:14:02.748
(INAUDIBLE)

01:14:48.314 --> 01:14:49.274
(STABS)

01:14:50.674 --> 01:14:51.634
(GASPS)

01:14:54.755 --> 01:14:57.835
Harry! Harry! Please!

01:15:02.637 --> 01:15:04.397
I may need a little help.

01:15:04.437 --> 01:15:05.397
(DOORS BURSTING OPEN)

01:15:06.037 --> 01:15:09.358
Miss? Miss? I have an injured man
who could use a little help here.

01:15:09.398 --> 01:15:10.878
- What happened?
- He had an accident.

01:15:10.958 --> 01:15:13.038
- No, I did not.
- He sliced off the tip of his finger.

01:15:13.078 --> 01:15:14.318
- But it wasn't an accident.
- Bradley.

01:15:14.358 --> 01:15:15.519
- Bradley!
- I did this to myself on purpose.

01:15:15.599 --> 01:15:16.919
Bradley, shut up!

01:15:24.200 --> 01:15:25.400
Hold still.

01:15:27.680 --> 01:15:30.521
Do you mind
if I ask you a personal question?

01:15:31.281 --> 01:15:32.881
Can I ask you one?

01:15:33.521 --> 01:15:36.761
- Two, actually.
- That's only fair.

01:15:38.122 --> 01:15:39.082
Uh...

01:15:39.482 --> 01:15:40.882
You go first.

01:15:42.002 --> 01:15:44.002
Why did you do this to yourself?

01:15:47.963 --> 01:15:49.803
I wanted to feel,

01:15:50.883 --> 01:15:55.764
in my body,
as much pain as I feel in my heart.

01:16:05.525 --> 01:16:07.566
You have questions for me?

01:16:09.006 --> 01:16:10.366
What's your name?

01:16:11.446 --> 01:16:12.926
Margit.

01:16:13.006 --> 01:16:16.927
Margit? Where are you from?

01:16:17.007 --> 01:16:19.727
I'm Hungarian, from Budapest.

01:16:23.488 --> 01:16:24.568
Ah.

01:16:27.008 --> 01:16:29.689
What caused you this pain in your heart?

01:16:32.130 --> 01:16:33.330
My eyes.

01:16:36.691 --> 01:16:39.131
I had them closed for so long.

01:16:40.211 --> 01:16:42.571
Then when I finally opened them,

01:16:43.332 --> 01:16:44.332
(SIGHS)

01:16:44.412 --> 01:16:46.692
I wasn't ready for what they saw.

01:16:50.012 --> 01:16:51.173
Hey.

01:16:53.373 --> 01:16:58.454
Do you think love is a trick
nature plays on people

01:16:58.534 --> 01:17:01.254
so that we'll make more babies?

01:17:03.094 --> 01:17:05.575
Or do you think that it's everything,

01:17:06.975 --> 01:17:11.255
the only meaning there is to this

01:17:12.736 --> 01:17:14.136
crazy dream?

01:17:16.136 --> 01:17:17.056
(SIGHS)

01:17:18.096 --> 01:17:19.936
The second one.

01:17:21.017 --> 01:17:22.897
Which do you believe?

01:17:24.377 --> 01:17:26.257
Unfortunately,

01:17:28.018 --> 01:17:29.538
the second one.

01:17:29.658 --> 01:17:31.098
(LAUGHING)

01:17:34.058 --> 01:17:36.939
Do you want to have dinner
with me sometime?

01:17:41.219 --> 01:17:42.179
Oh.

01:17:43.060 --> 01:17:44.420
How is he?

01:17:47.340 --> 01:17:48.860
Do you want the good news or the bad?

01:17:48.940 --> 01:17:51.141
I don't think I can take
any more bad news.

01:17:51.181 --> 01:17:54.061
Well, the good news is
his finger's gonna be all right.

01:17:54.101 --> 01:17:56.021
And the bad news?

01:17:57.222 --> 01:17:59.462
Bradley's in love again.

01:18:11.624 --> 01:18:13.145
All right, guys.

01:18:14.545 --> 01:18:17.425
JANEY: Come on, look at the camera.
Hi, wave.

01:18:17.505 --> 01:18:18.705
Hi, Janey.

01:18:18.865 --> 01:18:22.666
<i>Getting out of bed</i>

01:18:24.986 --> 01:18:27.347
Harry, I took your advice.

01:18:27.427 --> 01:18:28.907
What advice?

01:18:29.787 --> 01:18:31.307
I'm pregnant.

01:18:34.428 --> 01:18:35.948
Congratulations.

01:18:35.988 --> 01:18:37.068
- And you know what?
- What?

01:18:37.108 --> 01:18:40.628
We're gonna have another one.
Right away. Gonna have two.

01:18:40.708 --> 01:18:42.269
That's my girl.

01:18:42.429 --> 01:18:46.069
<i>'Cause your love is mine</i>

01:18:46.389 --> 01:18:47.909
JANEY: Say hi to the bride and groom.

01:18:47.989 --> 01:18:48.910
Hi!

01:18:49.630 --> 01:18:52.470
<i>Your love is all mine</i>

01:18:53.990 --> 01:18:56.431
What's making you smile like that?

01:18:56.551 --> 01:18:59.631
<i>Looking out the window</i>

01:19:00.351 --> 01:19:02.071
An unusual man.

01:19:04.152 --> 01:19:05.912
An innocent man.

01:19:07.552 --> 01:19:09.592
An open-hearted man.

01:19:11.953 --> 01:19:14.793
Someone who has given tremendous love

01:19:14.873 --> 01:19:16.713
but never had it returned.

01:19:19.354 --> 01:19:21.394
Not in the way he deserves.

01:19:21.474 --> 01:19:23.874
<i>Your love is mine</i>

01:19:27.355 --> 01:19:28.675
OSCAR: Hey, Chloe!

01:19:30.715 --> 01:19:32.396
This is you and me.

01:19:33.637 --> 01:19:36.317
<i>I've got this feeling</i>

01:19:36.557 --> 01:19:40.478
<i>That we'll always
be all right</i>

01:19:40.838 --> 01:19:42.678
<i>Yeah</i>

01:19:43.118 --> 01:19:46.238
<i>HARRY: You know
when two people belong together.</i>

01:19:46.278 --> 01:19:48.159
<i>Oscar and Chloe knew it.</i>

01:19:48.239 --> 01:19:50.199
<i>So did Bradley and Margit.</i>

01:19:51.279 --> 01:19:53.799
<i>Turns out that Bradley
finally found someone</i>

01:19:53.879 --> 01:19:56.800
<i>who loved him as much as he loved her.</i>

01:19:57.760 --> 01:19:59.400
<i>They fit together.</i>

01:20:00.440 --> 01:20:04.001
<i>It's a peculiar thing,
what happiness does for people.</i>

01:20:04.041 --> 01:20:07.001
<i>He actually became friends
with Kathryn and Jenny</i>

01:20:07.081 --> 01:20:08.761
<i>and Diana and David.</i>

01:20:10.242 --> 01:20:12.962
<i>Bradley realized that</i>

01:20:13.002 --> 01:20:15.442
<i>you can't hold someone's love
against them.</i>

01:20:15.762 --> 01:20:16.962
(PEOPLE CHEERING)

01:20:27.884 --> 01:20:29.524
And hut!

01:20:32.245 --> 01:20:33.605
PLAYER: Yes!

01:20:33.685 --> 01:20:35.045
Go right.

01:20:35.925 --> 01:20:37.485
- Almost got it.
- Okay...

01:20:37.565 --> 01:20:39.646
PLAYER 2: Don't let him
get around the outside, man.

01:20:43.326 --> 01:20:46.406
DAVID: I'll make a hand-off to Craig and
cross at the middle. Okay, Oscar, you...

01:20:46.446 --> 01:20:49.287
- Hey, Romeo. You with us?
- All right.

01:20:49.367 --> 01:20:52.647
The defender should bite.
Head for the end zone. Game over, okay?

01:20:52.687 --> 01:20:54.448
- On "69."
- All right.

01:20:58.928 --> 01:21:00.128
Hut!

01:21:06.250 --> 01:21:07.690
PLAYER 2: Get there.

01:21:07.770 --> 01:21:09.611
Get it! Get it! Get it!

01:21:15.771 --> 01:21:16.972
He got it!

01:21:19.732 --> 01:21:22.052
- And that's it.
- DIANA: Nice work, baby!

01:21:25.533 --> 01:21:26.653
Oscar?

01:21:27.253 --> 01:21:28.373
Oscar?

01:21:29.173 --> 01:21:30.413
Oscar?

01:21:32.854 --> 01:21:34.014
What happened?

01:21:34.094 --> 01:21:35.974
Hey. Hey, Oscar.

01:21:36.734 --> 01:21:38.174
You all right?

01:21:38.255 --> 01:21:39.975
He's not breathing. Somebody call 911!

01:21:40.015 --> 01:21:42.615
He's gonna be fine. He's gonna be just fine.

01:21:42.695 --> 01:21:44.135
I'm a doctor.

01:21:45.295 --> 01:21:47.936
You're gonna be okay. We're all right here.

01:21:48.016 --> 01:21:49.416
It's okay.

01:21:50.016 --> 01:21:51.456
It's okay.

01:21:51.816 --> 01:21:53.177
He's okay.

01:21:54.657 --> 01:21:55.617
(GRUNTS)

01:21:57.457 --> 01:21:59.297
Okay, I've got a pulse.
Let's get him to St. Luke's.

01:21:59.377 --> 01:22:02.618
- Get the car.
- You're gonna be just fine, okay?

01:22:02.698 --> 01:22:03.778
Okay?

01:22:05.698 --> 01:22:06.898
Please?

01:22:12.739 --> 01:22:14.099
MARGIT: Careful!

01:22:14.139 --> 01:22:17.540
This is Dr. Vekashi. I'm coming in
with a witnessed cardiac arrest.

01:22:17.620 --> 01:22:18.900
It's going to be all right.

01:22:18.940 --> 01:22:21.340
MAN: Come on, come on, come on!
DIANA: Okay?

01:22:22.901 --> 01:22:25.741
- MARGIT: Okay.
- All right, go. Go, go, go, go.

01:22:26.661 --> 01:22:28.261
Outta the way, outta the way.
Outta the way.

01:22:28.341 --> 01:22:29.621
(HONKING)

01:22:36.743 --> 01:22:38.544
The patient is barely breathing.

01:22:38.584 --> 01:22:40.024
MARGIT: Weak pulse.
CHLOE: Breathe!

01:22:40.104 --> 01:22:41.744
Have the cardiac team ready.

01:22:42.264 --> 01:22:43.704
BRADLEY: Shit! Get out of the fucking way!

01:22:43.744 --> 01:22:44.985
Go! Go!

01:22:46.265 --> 01:22:47.345
Goddamn it!

01:22:50.905 --> 01:22:52.266
(HONKING)

01:22:52.346 --> 01:22:53.746
Goddamn it!

01:22:54.626 --> 01:22:57.826
He's not breathing! He's not breathing!

01:22:59.867 --> 01:23:03.347
- Please make him breathe.
- Come on, Bradley. He won't last.

01:23:03.387 --> 01:23:04.747
Help! Please!

01:23:07.428 --> 01:23:08.668
(SOBBING) No!

01:23:36.472 --> 01:23:38.952
(MINISTER PREACHING
INDISTINCTLY)

01:26:14.935 --> 01:26:16.255
Bradley?

01:26:18.055 --> 01:26:19.456
Hey.

01:26:22.536 --> 01:26:24.856
I had a feeling I might find you here.

01:26:28.217 --> 01:26:30.177
I figured after today...

01:26:34.018 --> 01:26:35.858
It was awful, wasn't it?

01:26:36.258 --> 01:26:37.538
It was too sad.

01:26:40.098 --> 01:26:41.499
Unspeakable.

01:26:44.739 --> 01:26:47.459
God is either dead or he despises us.

01:26:50.620 --> 01:26:52.740
You don't really believe that.

01:26:55.100 --> 01:26:56.261
Maybe.

01:26:59.461 --> 01:27:02.141
I saw the most remarkable thing just now.

01:27:03.822 --> 01:27:05.863
I wandered into the stadium.

01:27:08.183 --> 01:27:12.584
I thought I was alone,
but down on the 50-yard line

01:27:12.664 --> 01:27:15.864
there was a young couple making love.

01:27:18.185 --> 01:27:20.905
I watched for longer than I should have.

01:27:24.225 --> 01:27:25.786
I was envious.

01:27:28.946 --> 01:27:31.266
And then I felt sorry for them.

01:27:33.987 --> 01:27:36.387
There's so much they don't know.

01:27:39.588 --> 01:27:42.148
Heartbreak they can't even imagine.

01:27:47.389 --> 01:27:48.349
(SIGHS)

01:27:49.429 --> 01:27:53.109
Well, even if they knew,
it wouldn't change anything.

01:27:53.189 --> 01:27:54.390
How so?

01:27:57.190 --> 01:28:00.910
Well, Chloe knew
what was gonna happen to Oscar.

01:28:00.990 --> 01:28:03.271
- What do you mean she knew?
- She did.

01:28:03.351 --> 01:28:08.071
She went to some psychic lady
who predicted the whole thing.

01:28:09.752 --> 01:28:11.312
She believed her?

01:28:12.072 --> 01:28:13.352
Yes, Harry.

01:28:14.632 --> 01:28:15.832
She did.

01:28:17.073 --> 01:28:18.673
And she didn't run away.

01:28:19.593 --> 01:28:21.753
She didn't crawl into a hole.

01:28:24.114 --> 01:28:25.914
She found them a house,

01:28:27.234 --> 01:28:30.554
she threw away her birth control,
and she married him.

01:28:35.355 --> 01:28:37.476
God doesn't hate us, Harry.

01:28:39.197 --> 01:28:42.477
If he did, he wouldn't have
made our hearts so brave.

01:29:05.120 --> 01:29:06.080
(BRANCHES RUSTLING)

01:29:20.362 --> 01:29:22.002
Hello, Bat.

01:29:22.082 --> 01:29:24.243
Who the fuck are you?

01:29:24.283 --> 01:29:26.163
Harry Stevenson.

01:29:26.203 --> 01:29:28.683
I don't think we've had the pleasure.

01:29:29.283 --> 01:29:30.524
What's that?

01:29:32.564 --> 01:29:34.324
What do you think?

01:29:36.244 --> 01:29:37.925
Well, what's it for?

01:29:38.645 --> 01:29:41.965
- For that whore that killed my boy.
- Now, wait a minute.

01:29:42.005 --> 01:29:45.206
I was told that that was because of
a congenital heart defect.

01:29:45.246 --> 01:29:48.246
I don't need to listen to that crap!
I got business here.

01:29:50.606 --> 01:29:51.806
So do I.

01:29:51.886 --> 01:29:52.847
(GROANS)

01:29:54.967 --> 01:29:56.727
Now, listen to me.

01:29:56.767 --> 01:29:59.728
You are not to bother that girl ever again.
You understand me?

01:29:59.808 --> 01:30:01.928
You are not to blame her
for your miserable life.

01:30:02.008 --> 01:30:07.129
You do, and I'll kill you myself. I swear it.
Now get the hell out of here. Go on!

01:30:14.811 --> 01:30:16.091
Harry?

01:30:16.411 --> 01:30:19.771
- It was the Bat, wasn't it?
- It's all right. He's gone.

01:30:23.852 --> 01:30:26.172
- You okay?
- Yeah.

01:30:37.894 --> 01:30:39.174
Chloe...

01:30:43.014 --> 01:30:47.255
You asked me
if Esther and I would be your parents.

01:30:53.896 --> 01:30:56.456
I thought you were just being kind
to an old man

01:30:56.536 --> 01:31:00.097
after I told you about the death of my son,

01:31:02.257 --> 01:31:04.017
so I didn't answer.

01:31:05.897 --> 01:31:11.618
And I didn't know that you already knew
that terrible things were going to happen.

01:31:18.499 --> 01:31:21.500
Esther and I want you to come
and live with us.

01:31:22.940 --> 01:31:24.580
Be our little girl.

01:31:33.221 --> 01:31:34.581
Say yes.

01:31:35.862 --> 01:31:37.582
Please say yes.

01:31:39.863 --> 01:31:40.863
Yes.

01:31:42.303 --> 01:31:43.384
Yes.

01:31:44.744 --> 01:31:45.704
(CRYING)

01:31:51.265 --> 01:31:52.385
Yes.

01:31:53.545 --> 01:31:58.426
Esther and I will give you and your baby
all the love we have left to give.

01:32:01.746 --> 01:32:03.266
Let's go home.

01:32:10.067 --> 01:32:13.188
<i>HARRY: The unexpected is always upon us.</i>

01:32:14.548 --> 01:32:17.228
<i>And of all the gifts arrayed before me,</i>

01:32:17.308 --> 01:32:21.789
<i>this one thought at this moment in my life
is the most precious.</i>

01:32:23.469 --> 01:32:27.109
<i>And so, we begin again.</i>

